subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Clypeus quadridentate, outer clypeal teeth reduced in size and deflexed outwards; genae serrated and discontinuous from clypeus (
figure 24
); protibia hardly sexually dimorphic, protibial spurs sinusoidal in males and straight in females (
figure 42
); small (length 
23 mm
; width 
14.24 mm
), black; elytra granular to smooth, markedly flat and deeply striate; metatarsal claws equal in length to last tarsal segment.
